The article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney on August 13, 2012. Carney discusses President Obama's plans to tour a farm in Missouri Valley, Iowa to see the impact of the drought. The President will announce that the Department of Agriculture will buy up to $170 million worth of meat and poultry to help farmers and ranchers during this critical time. Carney also addresses questions about the farm bill, Medicare, foreign policy, and the Olympics.